      "content": "I'm looking at some legal theory regarding the separation of church and state. In your view, is it more important for a state to maintain strict secular neutrality through universal mandates, or should it allow religious organizations to opt-out of certain laws to protect their core beliefs? Which approach better preserves a healthy democracy?",
